I am Sarxos, a level 60 Sorcerer. I can understand the frustration most of us feel with wizards, and unfortunately this is also deemed class envy of druids. Why they think this I am unsure, but they must say it for a reason. Perhaps they envy us in some way and they are applying reverse phsycology. Basically, i dont want to be a high druid. If i did, i would have played one to level 60 like my wizard and in less time.<br>
<br>
Druids are common, are the most played class in relation to other classes, and they are this because they can do a lot of varied things that appeal to groups. They can also solo with almost zero risk, which makes me wonder why they die at all. They are have received the lion's share of class balancing because it appeals to a wider audience than the lesser classes, so it the bang for the buck approach. Can't blame verant for wanting to please the most people at one time.<br>
<br>
For me, my wizard is not as primary as he was. I have discovered new-found motivation in EQ by playing my bard to a reasonably high level. One day I hope he is knocking on the door of 60 too. Unfortunately as he gets higher, I will only play my wizard when he is needed or wanted, and we know how often that will be.<br>
<br>
It is hard to rant about a wizard because having made 60 with one, I have to say I had my best times in eq with the wizard. Don't forget the social aspect of the game, your friends dont care that you are a wizard or shaman or whatever, you will still be in the group unless specifics are needed like in a dungeon environment.<br>
<br>
As for wizard class balancing, i am past caring. Really doesnt matter anymore. Verant will do what they do and work on what they see as a priority. I am sorry to say that we aren't it.<br>
<br>
Sarxos<br>
